<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-748-726  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 748 726.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  August 13 1990 v24 n33 p74(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>The info is better, but they miss the sound of ticker tape.andO;(Philips Petroleum Co., DEC)(information screening)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Maglitta, Joseph.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Organizations such as Phillips Petroleum Co and DEC are lookingfor ways to handle and sort through vast amounts of information.andO;The goal is to find a means to screen out all unwanted informationso the user can locate that which he/she is interested in.andO;Phillips uses a microcomputer which is a dedicated terminal forDesktop Data's information screening service, News Edge.andP;  Feedsfrom such major newswires as Dow Jones, PC Newswire, United PressInternational, Reuters, Comtex Scientific Corp and Knight-RidderInc are transmitted into a special microcomputer where softwaresearches the information for designated keywords.andP;  Articlescontaining the keywords are placed in an 'alert' database.andP;  DECuses Individual Inc's First news database.andP;  First evaluates theinformation it receives and locates, filters and transmitscustomized news via a channel such as MCI Mail.andP;  The user receivesinformation in a condensed form.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Phillips Petroleum Co. (information services)Digital Equipment Corp. (information services)Desktop Data Inc. (services)Individual Inc. (products).andO;Ticker:    DEC; P.andO;Product:   First (Data base) (usage).andO;Topic:     Information Resources ManagementInformation servicesNews Edge (Information retrieval system).andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>